   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 59, 59.346796}", 
    "history" -> {"13", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"quantum theory of measurement"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Tech Note", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "The no-cloning theorem dictates that it is impossible to make a copy of \
an unknown quantum state. 'You can clone a sheep, but not a quantum state,' \
Zurek (2000) once declared. (Here, the sheep refers to Dolly, cloned by a \
research group; see Wilmut et al. (1997).) The theorem was discovered by \
Wootters and Zurek (1982). See also Section 1.3 of the Quantum Workbook \
(2022). Why is it impossible to make a copy of an unknown quantum state?", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "The No-Cloning Theorem", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
    "The No-Cloning Theorem", "type" -> "Tech Note", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/NoCloningTheorem"}},
